# Phase 3 — Core Product Features: Production-Quality UI & Backend Upgrades

Upgrade all Phase 1 scaffold pages (Dashboard, Search/Browse, Course Detail, Favorites, History, Source Management) from basic functional shells to **polished, feature-complete, premium implementations**. This phase also upgrades the backend analytics service from its Phase 1 stub to return real data, and adds missing backend capabilities (category-filtered course queries, full dashboard stats endpoint, Redis caching for hot queries).

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Category Filter UI**: The Courses/Search page currently has sort-by but no **category filter** or **provider filter** dropdowns. The ARU (Section 4.5) specifies: *"Filters: category, provider/source, rating, date added, expiry status."* I will add a collapsible filter panel with category, provider, and expiry status filters. The backend already supports `categoryId` and `providerId` query params. **Please confirm this scope.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dashboard "Recent Courses" Widget**: The current dashboard shows Active Sources and Recent Scraper Activity, but **no recent courses widget**. The ARU (Section 4.4) specifies: *"Landing view summarizing: newest courses, total courses tracked, active sources, courses expiring soon, and recent scraper activity."* I will add a "Newest Courses" card showing the 5 most recently discovered courses with thumbnails and "Get Course" links. **Please confirm.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Real-Time Source Management Feedback**: Currently, the Sources page triggers scrape/test/retry but provides no **toast notifications** or real-time feedback to the user. I will add a toast notification system (using a lightweight custom toast or shadcn `sonner`) so users see success/failure messages for every action. **Please confirm this addition.**

> [!WARNING]
> **No charting library**: The Phase 3 analytics page shows category/provider breakdowns as horizontal bar charts built with pure CSS `<div>` bars. The ARU mentions analytics (Phase 4 scope for time-series), but Phase 3's "Courses by Category" and "Courses by Provider" charts are already rendered with CSS — no new charting library is needed yet. Phase 4 may introduce `recharts` for time-series if needed.

