## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — History Auto-Recording**: When the user clicks "Get Course" on the Course Detail page, it currently records a `CLICKED` event. Should we also auto-record a `VIEWED` event when the user opens the Course Detail page (on mount)? This would mean the History page shows *every course the user looked at*, not just courses they clicked "Get Course" on. **Please confirm or reject.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — Course Card "Get Course" Click → History**: On the Courses grid page (not the detail page), clicking "Get Course" opens the coupon URL but does **not** record a history event. Should it? If yes, this means every "Get Course" click is tracked regardless of whether the user viewed the detail page first. **Please confirm.**

